name: places/ChIJpdkLpogR2jERblRENz2WINg/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUR3cFBTUFdREAE
text:
{'text': 'had extremely low expectations of this fast food sushi, but it surpassed expectations

thick slices of fresh sashimi!

they also had promotion for 1 for 1 anago, which seemed a lil sus (thought they could be clearing old stock) but it was sooo good and fresh. the shari even came seasoned! unfortunately there was a very gross curly hair in my shari :(

hope other donkis roll out the same train sushi concept!!!', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJpdkLpogR2jERblRENz2WINg/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNZM0oyeHZnRRAB
text: {'text': 'Laura (the chef) is great, the food that she served us were so lovely looking and she has such a nice and friendly personality. When she overheard that we have yet to get the refill our tea (totally understandable given peak hours) and took the initiative to get it herself for us. This was such a nice and touching gesture and we felt the attentiveness of the staff here :)', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJpdkLpogR2jERblRENz2WINg/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNndlBTdVVREAE
text: {'text': 'Arrived 1245pm on Saturday for lunch. No queue.\n\nTheir sets are fuss free but I prefer to order ala carte based on my preference. Service is good. Food is fresh, including sashimi. Price is reasonable for restaurant standards. Been returning whenever I’m nearby.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJpdkLpogR2jERblRENz2WINg/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNvcDVuc3dBRRAB
text: {'text': 'Not bad. Salmon was really good. Tuna ones were really subpar. For the price overall, not worth in my opinion given sushiro is about 3 minutes away in perennial business city. Cheaper, more variety and better overall', 'languageCode': 'en'}
